<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mongolia Courts Foreign Investors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, June 5 (Xinhua) -- A two-day international fair to
attract foreign investment in Mongolia's natural gas and mining
industries ended today.
</P>
<P>
Some 105 companies from 20 countries including China, the
United States, Canada, Britain and Russia, and more than 60
Mongolian companies attended the fair co-sponsored by the
Mongolian government and the World Bank.
</P>
<P>
The foreign companies were briefed on Mongolia's investment
policies and held talks with relevant Mongolian companies or
ministries on possible investment opportunities.
</P>
<P>
Although the Mongolian government had outlined a strategy of
attracting foreign investment to develop its domestic economy,
little progress has been made in recent years because of the poor
infrastructure and the lack of a comprehensive legal system.
</P>
<P>
Since 1990, foreign enterprises have invested only 123 million
U.S. dollars and set up 540 joint ventures in Mongolia.
</P>
<P>
In a bid to change the situation, the Mongolian government has
adopted some preferential policies including exemption from
taxation for all imports except tobacco and liquor and
simplification of customs formalities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
