<HEADLINE> 27 Killed in Road Accident in Central Thailand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, June 5 (Xinhua) -- At least 27 people were killed
today when a bus carrying 51 workers home after work fell into a
river in central Thailand's Lop Buri province.
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred when a tyre of the bus burst, a report
reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
Nine people were still missing, the report said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
