<HEADLINE> S. Africa Backs OAU Peacekeeping Efforts in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, June 5 (Xinhua) -- South Africa today supported
the Organization of African Unity (OAU) to give the go-ahead to a
government of Sierra Leone.
</P>
<P>
The ruling African National Congress (ANC) said in a statement
that the OAU resolution on Sierra Leone peacekeeping force was a
clear message that Africa would not tolerate undemocratic,
dictatorial and militaristic regimes.
</P>
<P>
Sierra Leonean rebel soldiers, headed by Johanny Paul Koroma,
ousted the civilian government led by President Ahmad Tejan
Kabbah on May 25.
</P>
<P>
The military coup was immidiately denounced by the
international society, especially African countries. On June 2,
a 3,600-strong West Afrcian Peacekeeping force started imposing
military intervention against the Sierra Leonean coupmakers.
</P>
</TEXT>
