<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CPPCC Chairman Starts Visit to Germany </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MUNICH, June 5 (Xinhua) -- China and Germany have enjoyed good
relations with frequent political contacts and expanding
cooperation in recent years, Li Ruihuan, chairman of the Chinese
People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC) said today.
</P>
<P>
He was speaking on his arrival in Munich, the capital
of the German state Bavaria, for a seven-day official
goodwill visit to Germany, the first by a CPPCC chairman.
</P>
<P>
He was greeted at the airport by the state secretary of the
Ministry for Economy, Transportation and Technology of Bavaria,
Hans Spitzer and Chinese ambassador to Germany Lu Qiutian.
</P>
<P>
During his visit, Li is scheduled to meet German President
Roman Herzog, Chancellor Helmut Kohl, Foreign Minister Klaus
Kinkel, and Rita Suessmuth, president of the Bundestag (the lower
house of parliament).
</P>
<P>
He will hold talks with them on bilateral ties and other issues
of common interest. He will also visit enterprises in Munich and
Berlin.
</P>
<P>
Li said he hopes that his visit will help promote mutual
understanding between the Chinese and German peoples and deepen
friendship and cooperation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Germany is the last leg of Li's three-nation Europe tour,
which has already taken him to Portugal and Greece.
</P>
<P>
After his departure from Athens, Greece, Li sent a telegram to
Greek parliament speaker Apostolos Kaklamanis, expressing great
satisfaction with the results of his visit to Greece.
</P>
<P>
He said he believes that there are broad prospects of further
growth of Sino-Greek relations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
