<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-05 16:14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iraq Raps AL's Indifference over Turkish Incursion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Iraqi Foreign Minister Saeed
al-Sahhaf today complained to the Cairo-based Arab League(AL)
about its indifference over Turkey's recent military incursion
into northern Iraq.
</P>
<P>
He voiced the grievance in a message sent to AL Secretary
General Esmat Abdel Meguid by Iraq's permanent representative to
the league Nabil Nejm today.
</P>
<P>
"The Turkish shelling of Iraqi towns and villages is an
outright violation of our territorial integrity and runs counter
to the principles of good neighborliness," Sahhaf said in the
message detailing the ongoings in northern Iraq.
</P>
<P>
Sahhaf also criticized the AL Council's "indifferent stance."
With the support of air bombing and artillery fire, about 25,000
to 50,000 Turkish troops have pushed across the border into
northern Iraq assaulting the Kurdistan Workers Party (PKK) rebels
since May 14.
</P>
<P>
Warning that such practices will shake the stability of the
Middle East, however, he said the league itself showed "no
interest towards the Turkish invasion of north Iraq."
</P>
<P>
Iraq retains its legitimate right to respond to Turkish
offensives and to request compensation for the damages inflicted
on the Iraqi people, he added.
</P>
<P>
He called on the Turkish government to re-examine its policies
towards northern Iraq and establish cooperation on the basis of
good neighborliness and mutual respect of sovereignty.
</P>
<P>
In a related development, Chief of Staff of the Turkish Armed
Forces General Ismail Haqqi ordered all army commanders not to
leave the country and put off any external visits to the end of
August, according to press reports reaching here today.
</P>
<P>
The orders came at a time when the Turkish forces that crossed
into north Iraq for the destruction of all PKK bases are reported
to remain there until the end of August.
</P>
<P>
The Arab League and regional countries have condemned the
continued Turkish incursion and urged an immediate troop
withdrawal. Turkey defended its move as purely designed to purge
the Kurdish rebels. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
