<DOCNO> XIE19970606.0009 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Polish Parliament Approves Anti-corruption Bill </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Poland's senior officials and
lawmakers will have to report their earnings and those of their
spouses under a bill passed today by the lower house of parliament.
</P>
<P>
The president will have to file his earning statement to the
chairman of the Supreme Court.
</P>
<P>
The bill also prohibits the president, government ministers,
parliamentary speakers and almost all senior state employees from
holding stakes of more than 10 percent in any company.
</P>
<P>
They will also be banned from sitting on company boards and
doing business.
</P>
<P>
They are also required to report all gifts and foreign junkets
received while in office.
</P>
<P>
Earnings data will be kept confidential but reports on presents
and foreign trips paid by others will be available to all, the
bill said.
</P>
<P>
The bill must be passed by the Senate and signed by the
president to become law. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
