<DOCNO> XIE19970606.0010 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Leader Meets Greek Foreign Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Chairman of the National Committee
of the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference Li
Ruihuan said today that through his visit to Greece he deeply
feels the Sino-Greek friendship has a profound social foundation.
</P>
<P>
During his meeting with Greek Foreign Minister Theodoros
Pangalos here today, Li also said the friendly relations between
China and Greece have proved the truth that in the state-to-state
exchanges, the principles of mutual respect, mutual understanding
and mutual support should be followed.
</P>
<P>
He said countries, big or small, rich or poor, should be
treated on an equal footing. Under no pretext and by no means
should big countries bully the small ones, the strong one suppress
the weak ones, nor should one constrain the other, he said.
</P>
<P>
He also said that different countries have different historical
backgrounds, cultural traditions and styles of life, and
therefore, the policy-decision of each country is made according
to its actual conditions. Each country should try to understand
the decision of another country, he added.
</P>
<P>
He said it is also necessary for countries to inform each other
of the situation on major issues, coordinate and cooperate, and
help each other in times of difficulty.
</P>
<P>
In response, the Greek foreign minister said he shares views
with Li, stressing that only by treating each other on an equal
footing, can the issues of common concern to various countries be
solved reasonably.
</P>
<P>
Pangalos also said that as there is diversification in the
world culture, the world political power should be balanced and
multi-polarized. Greece stands for a unified and strong Europe in
the form of federation and Europe should be one of the
decision-making centers for international affairs, he added.
</P>
<P>
He said Greece opposes any form of hegemonism. He added that
China's cultural traditions, past sufferings and current state
policies have shown that it has not practiced, and will not
practice, hegemonism.
</P>
<P>
He said he believes that Greece and China share identical views
in this regard, which serves as a foundation for their friendly
bilateral ties and cooperation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
