<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kazakh President Calls for More Foreign Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA ATA, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Kazakh President Nursultan
Nazarbayev called for more foreign investment at a two-day
international conference on investment which opened here today.
</P>
<P>
The Kazakh economy needs massive foreign investment to continue
its growth and development, the president told the conference
attended by 80 executives from 58 well-known businesses and
commercial organizations.
</P>
<P>
Kazakhstan is making efforts to improve the investment
environment and will be able to clear all hurdles to foreign
investment by 2000, Nazarbayev said.
</P>
<P>
The president predicted inflation would be under 17 percent
this year and said the country's economy would see a gradual
recovery. The government has also implemented a liberalization
policy toward foreign trade.
</P>
<P>
The president said the prospect for developing mineral
resources and agriculture in Kazakhstan is bright.
</P>
<P>
The country, with rich natural resources, has the world's
largest uranium reserves and seventh largest gold reserves, he
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
