<HEADLINE> Chinese Leader Visits German Audi AG </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
INGOLSTADT, Germany, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Chinese leader Li
Ruihuan today paid a visit to the Ingolstadt plant of the German
carmaker Audi AG after arriving at the southern German city of
Munich for a seven-day official goodwill visit to the country.
</P>
<P>
Li, chairman of the National Committee of the Chinese People's
Political Consultative Conference, was greeted by Erich Schmitt,
member of the board of the Audi AG, at the plant, some 70
kilometers from Munich.
</P>
<P>
Schmitt made a detailed introduction of the Audi company, the
luxury division of Volkswagen and its cooperation with China, and
led the Chinese leader for a tour around the assembly lines.
</P>
<P>
Li expressed satisfaction with the cooperation between China
and the Audi company. He also made a few suggestions for technical
improvement and hoped that the existing cooperation would be
further improved.
</P>
<P>
Schmitt said the Asia-Pacific area, particularly China, has
become more and more important in recent years.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the latest milestones for the cooperation between
Volkswagen and China were facts that the total output of the
Volkswagen joint venture in Shanghai has broken the 800,000 mark
and Audi's joint venture with China's First Automotive Works in
the northern Chinese city of Changchun has also produced 100,000
Audi 100 cars.
</P>
<P>
"These have laid a sound foundation for our successful
development in China," Schmitt said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
