<HEADLINE> French PM to Balance Social Action, Growth With Euro </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 5 (Xinhua) -- French Prime Minister Lionel Jospin
is committed to his campaign promise to balance the relationship
of social action and economic growth with the plan to launch the
European single currency, euro, Minister for European Affairs
Pierre Moscovici said today.
</P>
<P>
"The commitment of Lionel Jospin will be held," Moscovici told
journalists when he was taking over the office of the Ministry for
European Affairs from his predecessor Michel Barnier.
</P>
<P>
Jospin promised to reorient France's policy on Europe by
emphasizing more on the social aspects of Europe and pushing
forward economic growth and job creation in France.
</P>
<P>
Moscovici said that Jospin based his legislative campaign on
the promise to maintain a balance between social construction in
France and its integration with the rest of Europe.
</P>
<P>
Jospin also said that European construction must conform with
the national interests of France.
</P>
<P>
"This means notably that on the basic issue of single currency
and growth, we will hold our commitments," said Moscovici, who
described as "indispensable" these conditions offered by France
for continuing to join the process of European integration.
</P>
<P>
Asked about the relationship between France and Germany, he
said that the Franco-German partnership remains "quite important,"
while the Franco-British relations could also be further
developed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
