<HEADLINE> Collaborative Efforts Called for in Environment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Chairman of the National
Environmental Management Council of Tanzania (NEMC) Reginal Mengi
today called for collaborative efforts for environmental
protection.
</P>
<P>
"Environmental conservation is not the duty of the government
alone. It is the duty of everybody. Let us from now on, bring our
efforts together in conserving our environment. Let us do that with
all efforts," Mengi stresed.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks in a paper on environmental degradation
and pollution in Tanzania at a workshop organised to mark the
World Enviornment Day.
</P>
<P>
Mengi said as it was insisted during the 1992 environmental
conference held in Rio De Janciro, efforts to conserve and protect the
environment would succeed only if everybody took part in implementing
environmental related plans and programs.
</P>
<P>
"If we want to win the war against poverty, we have to conserve our
environment. We will never attain the social and economic development
without taking care of the environment," he said.
</P>
<P>
The NEMC chairman said history showed that countries which
attained faster economic growth were those which were seriously
engaged in environmental conservation.
</P>
<P>
He mentioned unsustainable deforestation, improper land use,
improper disposal of industrial, hospital or domestic wastes, careless
use of insecticides and pestiicides and mining as some of the
activities which cause environmental degradation and pollution.
</P>
<P>
Mengi said environmental problems had serious impacts on the
lives of living things including the people.
</P>
<P>
He said the government had been taking various measures
to combat the problem including preparation of the environmental
policy and introduction of the environmental impact assessment unit.
</P>
<P>
During the workshop, Mengi presented certificates of
appreciation to Jitegemee Secondary School, Knoike Construction
Company, University of Dar es Sallam, Journalist Environmental
Association of Tanzania for their contribution in conserving and
protecting the environment. enditem

