<HEADLINE> German Unemployment Projected to Average 4.2 Mln </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Germany's Labor Office chief Bernhard
Jagoda today warned of an average joblessness in Germany at 4.2
million during 1997, exceeding the 3.95 million projected by the
Bonn government, according to press reports.
</P>
<P>
Jagoda said this on the periphery of a meeting in Dresden of
labor chiefs from the country's 16 states. His Nuremberg-based
office is expected to release May joblessness figures Friday.
</P>
<P>
The mass-circulation tabloid Bild reported today that Germany's
unemployment in May dropped from some 4.35 million, or 11.3
percent, in April to about 4.26 million. This is compared with 3.8
million in May 1996. 
</P>
