<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Earns More from Export in Last Nine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia earned 2.2 billion
Birr (about 328 million US Dollars) from export of coffee and
other traditional commodities during the past nine months, 306
million Birr more than that in the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
This was announced today by Ethiopian Minister of Trade and
Industry Kasahun Ayele in his third quarterly report to the
parliament.
</P>
<P>
Kasahun said the bulk of the export earning has been made from
coffee, skins and hides, oil seeds and grains.
</P>
<P>
The minsiter emphasized that 64 percent of the revenue generated
during the period was made by private exproters.
</P>
<P>
He said, about 1,700 exporters, importers and commission agents
were issued licences and the figure represented an almost 80
percent increase over last year's.
</P>
<P>
The minister added that in recognition of the pivotal role of
micro-enterprises in the economic advancement of the nation, a
national committee which is chaired by the prime minister has been
established. enditem

