<HEADLINE> IDB Launches Pound Sterling 200 Mln Bond Issue in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 5 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American Development
Bank (IDB) today announced the launching of a 200 million pound
sterling bond issue on the Euromarket for a three-year term and a
semiannual coupon of 6.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
The issue, which is equivalent to some 326 million U.S.
dollars, was priced at 99.1 percent and matures on June 26, 2000.
The issue is mainly targeted to retail investors in Japan.
</P>
