<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Algerian Elections in Full Swing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALGIERS, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Algeria's legislative elections
which began here this morning has been proceeding smoothly.
</P>
<P>
The Algerian Interior Ministry said in its announcement today
that 41.78 percent of the constituency had already cast their
votes.
</P>
<P>
According to well-informed sources close to the ministry, out
of the registered voters of 16.7 million, some 7 million went to
the polling stations throughout the country until 3:00 p.m. local
time (15:00 GMT) today.
</P>
<P>
Algerian expatriates also voted at the polling stations
abroad, the same sources added.
</P>
<P>
The voters were due to cast their ballots to elect the first
parliament under the multi-party system in Algeria ever since the
system was adopted in 1989.
</P>
<P>
There are so far 73 opposition political parties in
Algeria. Most of them were contesting in the elections.
</P>
<P>
The elections were conducted under the supervision of 240
observers from the United Nations, the Arab League and the
Organization of African Unity.
</P>
<P>
The ongoing elections in Algeria are considered an important
and decisive step aimed at achieving stability in the
terror-rampant country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
