<HEADLINE> Jordan Supports Palestinians Back to Their Homeland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, June 5 (Xinhua) -- King Hussein of Jordan said today
that the Palestinians in Jordan should finally settle down on
their own national soil.
</P>
<P>
During his visit to the Mu'ta area in southern Jordan, Hussein
stated that Jordan always supports the Palestinians to return to
their homeland in the West Bank and Gaza Strip.
</P>
<P>
Earlier last month, the King said in a speech that Jordan
would not be a substitute homeland for Palestinians and would not
tolerate any attempt to undermine Jordan's national unity.
</P>
<P>
His speech was directing against a 700-million U.S. dollars
plan by the United States Jewish society, under which the
Palestinian refugees should be permanently settled down in Jordan.
</P>
<P>
Jordan annually allocates some 300 million dollars for the
Palestinian refugees who came to Jordan after Israel annexed part
of their homeland in 1948 during the first Middle East war.
</P>
<P>
About one-fourth of Jordan's 4 million-strong population are
Palestinian refugees. 
</P>
