<HEADLINE> Fireworks Plant Explosion Claims Four </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Four people were killed in an
explosion at an east Tennessee fireworks plant and officials say
there may be more casualties.
</P>
<P>
State Fire Marshal Stuart Crine says at least three victims
died at the scene and the other died enroute to the University of
Tennessee Medical Center in Knoxville, news reports said.
</P>
<P>
The blast occurred at about noon Eastern time. Its force was
felt for several miles, and shattered the showroom windows of a
car dealership a mile away.
</P>
<P>
The total number of casualties is not confirmed, but officials
say between six and eight people were scheduled to work in the
plant at the time of the blast.
</P>
<P>
Crine says there appears to be no survivors. He says
investigators believe people were assembling the fireworks for an
upcoming fireworks display. 
