<HEADLINE> 2 Turkish Helicopters Downed by Russian-made </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, June 6 (Xinhua) -- A Turkish high-ranking military
officer said here today that a Super Cobra helicopter and a
Cougar helicopter were downed in northern Iraq by Russian-made
land-to-air SA-7B missiles.
</P>
<P>
Erol Ozkasnak, secretary general of the General Staff of
Turkey, made the remarks at a press conference. He did not give
the details.
</P>
<P>
He said that two pilots were killed when the Super Cobra
helicopter was downed at the south of Cukurca town of Hakkari on
May 18.
</P>
<P>
However, a statement by the General Staff of Turkey said
Wednesday that due to a technical failure, a Cougar helicopter of
the Turkish armed forces crashed in Zap region of northern Iraq,
killing eight officers, two noncommissioned officers and one
soldier.
</P>
<P>
About 50,000-strong Turkish government troops have carried out
cross-border military operations in northern Iraq since May 14
to wipe out the PKK establishment there.
</P>
<P>
Turkish military officials have said that at least 2,000 PKK
members have been killed in the military campaign in northern
Iraq, but the PKK claimed that its losses were less than 100
people.
</P>
<P>
The PKK has been fighting an almost 13-year-old separatist
war for autonomy, which has claimed over 23,000 lives in eastern
and southeastern Turkey since August 1984. 
</P>
