<HEADLINE> EU Annual Inflation Down in April </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, June 6 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) annual
inflation rate fell to 1.5 percent in April, following the drop
from 2 percent in February to 1.7 percent in March, it was learned
here today.
</P>
<P>
The rate, well down from 2.6 percent recorded in April last
year, was calculated as an average of the Harmonized Indices of
Consumer Prices (HICPs) of EU member states, according to
Eurostat, the EU's statistical office.
</P>
<P>
Lowest April rates were registered in Belgium and Finland both
with 0.9 percent, to be followed by France with 1.0 percent and
Luxembourg with 1.1 percent, Eurostat reported. 
</P>
