<HEADLINE> India to Provide Nepal Transit to Bangladeshi Port </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, June 6 (Xinhua) -- India has agreed to provide Nepal
a transit route to Bangladesh on a trial basis, the Nepali Foreign
Ministry said here today.
</P>
<P>
During his meeting with Nepali Foreign Minister Prakash Chandra
Lohani today, visiting Indian Prime Minister I. K. Gujral agreed
to provide the transit route for Nepali exports to Bangladeshi
ports via eastern India, the ministry said in a press release.
</P>
<P>
At the meeting, the Nepali foreign minister emphasized that the
transit route is not only for Nepal's economic development but
also for creating an atmosphere of confidence between the two
neighboring countries and realizing the concept of sub-regional
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Nepal has been asking India to provide the Phulbari overland
corridor for its products to be shipped to Bangladeshi ports, thus
significantly cutting the transportation cost of its exports.
</P>
<P>
Currently most of Nepal's exports and imports are shipped
through the Indian port of Calcutta.  
</P>
