<HEADLINE> Four Myanmar Citizens Executed In China For Drug Trafficking </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Four citizens of Myanmar who were
found guilty of drug trafficking in China and were sentenced to
death and executed in Yunnan Province today, according to the
Superme People's Court.
</P>
<P>
The four, Hui Xuehua, Zhang Yinfu, Chen Jiaxi and Lu Xiaofa,
who were all of Chinese origin, had entered Yunnan Province in
southwest China with nearly 38,000 grams of heroin in early
1993. Two of them, Hui and Zhang, were armed with a handgun and a
grenade, and wounded a Chinese policeman in the process.
</P>
<P>
Liu Jiachen, vice president of the Supreme People's Court,
reiterated China's resoluteness in dealing with international drug
trafficking and said that China will continue to severely crack
down on drug dealers.  
