<HEADLINE> Majority Satisfied With HK's Situation: Survey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Most of Hong Kong residents are
satisfied with the present situation in Hong Kong, a latest public
opinion survey shows.
</P>
<P>
The survey conducted by the government Home Affairs Branch
(HAB) in May indicates that 78 percent of the 1,503 respondents
expressed satisfaction with the situation in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
This represented an increase of two percentage points over the
last survey conducted in March, an HAB spokesman said today.
</P>
<P>
Twenty percent of the respondents expected the situation to
improve in the next 12 months while 50 percent believed it would
remain almost the same.
</P>
<P>
When asked if they think Hong Kong would continue to be
prosperous and stable, 72 percent expressed confidence, almost
unchanged from the 73 percent in March.
</P>
<P>
Concerning the biggest problem facing Hong Kong, 60 percent of
the respondents cited housing while 21 percent mentioned
welfare-related problems and 19 percent labor-related issues.
</P>
