<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 6 (Xinhua) -- New orders in Britain's construction
industry fell 2 percent in the three months to the end of April
over the previous three months, with private housing and
infrastructure particularly hard hit, the Environment Department
said today.
</P>
<P>
Private housing orders declined by 23 percent in the three
months and showed only 3 percent increase over the same period
last year.
</P>
<P>
However, construction orders registered an 8 percent increase
over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The department said that construction orders from industrial
and private commercial sectors increased "sharply" in April.
</P>
<P>
The seasonally adjusted value of orders, rose to 2.06 billion
pounds (3.296 billion U.S. dollars) in April compared with 1.88
billion pounds (3.008 billion dollars) in March. 
