<HEADLINE> Economic Cooperation Symposium In East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, June 6 (Xinhua) -- A symposium on economic
cooperation between east China's Zhejiang Province and Hong Kong
opened today in the provincial capital of Hangzhou.
</P>
<P>
The symposium was jointly sponsored by the Zhejiang Provincial
Youth Federation, the Provincial Department of Foreign Trade and
Economic Cooperation, the Provincial Tourism Administration, and
the Provincial Academy of Social Sciences.
</P>
<P>
About 40 scholars from the People's Bank of China, the
National Tourism Administration, and the State Planning Commission
attending it said that Zhejiang and Hong Kong have expanded their
economic and trade relations over the past few years.
</P>
<P>
There is still potential for economic cooperation between the
two areas. They say that the two regions can work together in
resources, products, markets, trade, investment, and tourism after
Hong Kong's return to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong is Zhejiang's important trade partner and had set up
6,594 companies in Zhejiang by the end of 1996, with a total
investment of 8.8 billion US dollars, nearly 48 percent of the
total of overseas-funded projects and 53 percent of the
investment, respectively.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, Zhejiang has 2.46 billion US dollars worth of trade
with Hong Kong, and had 127,800 Hong Kong and Macao
tourists. 
</P>
