<HEADLINE> Former Senior Official Sentenced to Five Years For Bribery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 6 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Communist Party Central
Commission For Discipline Inspection issued a circular today,
calling on leaders at all levels to learn a lesson from the
downfall of a senior official of Hainan Province and to be clean
and true Communist Party members.
</P>
<P>
Wei Zefang, former vice-chairman of the Standing Committee of
the Hainan Provincial People's Congress, was sentenced by the
Provincial Higher People's Court to five years in prison and
expelled from the Communist Party for accepting 60,000 yuan in
bribes while serving as the secretary of the Provincial Political
and Legal Committee. He was also accused of tampering with an
investigation of the businessmen who was accused of bribing him.
</P>
<P>
Wei was a communist member for 39 years and has 47 years of
work experience.
</P>
<P>
"He has done some good things for the Party and the people
during his long period of revolutionary work," the circular said,
"but, in the late years, he failed to preserve his integrity, and
accepted bribes and covered up for criminals, and ended up as a
prisoner himself."
</P>
<P>
"The lesson is a profound one and one that cadres at all levels
must draw on," it said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
