<HEADLINE> Record High Temperatures In Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 6 (Xinhua) -- The temperature climbed to a high
of 37.2 centigrade today in Shanghai Municipality, half a degree
higher than the record set during the same month in 1945.
</P>
<P>
Yesterday, the temerature was 35.6 centigrade, the first day
this year for it to go above 35 degrees in Shanghai. In May, the
average was 22.8 degrees centigrade, compared with 18.9 for the
same month in most years years in the city.
</P>
<P>
Local experts attribute the early high temperature to the
current warm continental air mass in the area. A cooling down is
likely as a minor cold-front moves southward, they said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
