<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Receives More Tourists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong has registered
increases in both tourist arrivals and tourist income so far this
year, according to statistics released today by the Hong Kong
Tourist Association (HKTA).
</P>
<P>
In April alone, more than 1.048 million tourists visited Hong
Kong, a 10.8 percent rise over the same month last year, while in
the first four months the total number of tourist arrivals reached
3.9 million, up 9.5 percent from a year earlier.
</P>
<P>
In the first quarter of this year, income from tourism amounted
to 20.8 billion HK dollars (2.67 billion U.S. dollars), 3.5
percent more than in the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
The HKTA forecasts that the total tourist arrivals for 1997
will reach 12.4 million, a percent increase over last year's
11.7 million.  
</P>
</TEXT>
