<HEADLINE> 6 Killed in Bus Blast in Northern India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Six persons were killed and seven
others injured when a powerful bomb exploded in a private bus
bound for Himachal Pradesh in northern India this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Reports reaching here said that the explosion occurred minutes
after the bus started from the local bus station. None of the dead
has been identified so far while the injured have been admitted in
a local hospital.
</P>
<P>
Police said that the bomb appeared to be similar to the one
which had exploded in an Indian-held Jammu and Kashmir Road
Transport Corporation bus in the first week of April. Four persons
were killed and 14 injured in that blast.
</P>
<P>
The local authorities suspended the traffic immediately and
summoned the help of the army as they feared more bombs to have
been planted in other buses also, the reports said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
