<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zhou Xiaoqing Takes Two Titles in Rhythmic Gymnastics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SYDNEY, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Zhou Xiaoqing of China became the
double champion when she won both the loop and ribbon events here
on Friday at the Four Continents Championships in Rhythmic
Gymnastics.
</P>
<P>
Zhou, an Olympian at Atlanta, scored the tournment-high 9.500
points to take the loop title with her perfect performance, and
bagged home her second with 9.366 points in the ribbon finals.
</P>
<P>
Japan also reap good harvest by halving the six golds at stake,
taking the titles in the rope, five-member ball and the three-ball
and two-ribbon finals.
</P>
<P>
The other gold medal was snatched by Canada in the ribbon
event.
</P>
<P>
As the four-day championships concluded Friday, Japan ranked
first with six golds, four silvers and three bronzes, beating
China to second on three golds and three silvers. 
</P>
