<HEADLINE> Souvenir Badges Commemorate Hong Kong's Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, June 6 (Xinhua) -- A total of 97,000 sets of souvenir
bronze badges for commemorating the return of Hong Kong to the
motherland on July 1 went on sale in inland areas, and in Hong
Kong and Macao today.
</P>
<P>
Each set has a larger badge and four smaller ones. The larger
is 50 mm in diameter, and has a silver rim and gilded face. The
front shows ornamental columns symbolizing the Chinese nation, and
ribbons decorated with Chinese redbuds on the columns symbolizing
the return of Hong Kong to the motherland. Around them are "one
country, two systems" in Chinese and English.
</P>
<P>
The smaller ones are 40 mm in diameter and show the national
flag, regional flag, a full moon, a flying bird, children, Hong
Kong bay, and other symbols.
</P>
<P>
The badges were made at the Shenyang Mint, in the capital of
Liaoning Province, with the approval of the Hong Kong and Macao
Affairs Office of the State Council. Experts said they are
valuable collection items. 
