<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 6 (Xinhua) -- The governments of Hong Kong and
the Republic of Indonesia signed an air services agreement today.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong government said in a press release that the
agreement would provide the necessary legal framework to ensure
that Hong Kong's air links with Indonesia would continue smoothly
beyond June 30, 1997.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong's Secretary for Economic Services Stephen Ip said the
economic and tourism links between Hong Kong and Indonesia are
strong. He hoped to see the close aviation links between the two
places continue to grow in the years ahead.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong's flagcarrier Cathay Pacific currently operates 19
return services per week to Indonesia while Garuda Indonesia
operates 17 return flights per week to Hong Kong. The two airlines
together carried a total of 560,000 passengers in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The agreement is the 21st of its kind signed by Hong Kong.
