<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Middle East Business Briefs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, June 6 (Xinhua) -- The following are business briefs
from Middle East countries.
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- A new electric light motor for propelling bicycles
has been developed in Israel, according to the English bi-weekly
The Jerusalem Report.
</P>
<P>
The motor, which weighs 1.3 pounds (0.59 kilograms)
and costs less than 100 U.S. dollars, fits under
the saddle and propels the back wheel.
</P>
<P>
A California company which supplies bikes to local police
forces is now testing it, and has promised big orders if
the tests go well.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, with this motor, a bicycle can reach
the speed of 30 kilometers per hour.
</P>
<P>
ANKARA -- High inflation rate is expected to continue in the
coming months in Turkey, a recent Daily News report said.
</P>
<P>
According to the figures released by the State Institute of
Statistics Wednesday, the consumer price index in May increased
4.7 percent over that of April.
</P>
<P>
The most surprising jump was a 31.5 percent rise in the
price of onions, a 782.5 percent increase, compared with the same
period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Also among the biggest price hikes, were the 11.5 percent rise
in the cost of women's ready-made garments, and a 3.7 percent
increase in tobacco and alcohol.
</P>
<P>
The grave devaluation of the Turkish lira, legal tender of Turkey,
adds to the worsening situation of inflation. At present, the
exchange rate of the Turkish lira is 142,870 to one against the
U.S. dollar.
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- The Muslim-8 Group closed its meeting in Cairo
Wednesday after endorsing an Egyptian proposal on the
international company for trade and marketing among the member
countries, the Egyptian newspaper Al-Ahram said today.
</P>
<P>
The paper quoted Sayed Qassam Al-Masri, Egyptian assistant
foreign minister for multilateral relations and international
cooperation, as saying that several recommendations were made at
the meeting to be passed at the M-8 Group summit to be held in the
Turkish largest city of Istanbul on June 15.
</P>
<P>
The recommendations include setting up an international company
for trade and marketing among the M-8 countries in a bid to step
up trade exchange and preparing studies on the legal form of the
company, its structure and financial sources.
</P>
<P>
The M-8 Group comprises Turkey, Iran, Egypt, Indonesia,
Pakistan, Nigeria, Malaysia and Bangladesh.
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- Egypt signed a contract with Iraq Wednesday to export
37,500 tonnes of sugar that is worth 14 million U.S. dollars to the
sanctions-hit country, according to the Al-Ahram newspaper today.
</P>
<P>
Adel El-Shahawi, chairman of the Holding Company for Food and
Industries, said coordination will be made with the Egyptian
foreign ministry to make contacts with the United Nations in order
to adopt measures to secure the U.N. approval of the contract.
</P>
</TEXT>
