<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-Premier Meets Italian Prime Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Zhu Rongji
said today that China and Italy can raise bilateral friendly
relations of cooperation to a new level by further expanding their
cooperative fields, means and forms in the '90s, following their
efforts in the effective cooperation of the '80s.
</P>
<P>
Zhu made the remark in a meeting here this morning with
visiting Italian Prime Minister Romano Prodi.
</P>
<P>
He also said that Prodi, a well-known economist and an old
friend of China, has visited China several times and made positive
contributions to the development of bilateral friendship and
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said he is convinced that Prodi's current visit will
further enhance mutual understanding and trust, and will help to
increase bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
Recalling his last two visits to Italy, he said that Italy's
brilliant culture and arts, and economic achievements have left a
profound impression on him.
</P>
<P>
Noting that both China and Italy have ancient civilizations and
the two peoples have a long history of traditional friendship, Zhu
said that Sino-Italian relations in various fields have been
growing smoothly since the two countries established diplomatic
ties 26 years ago.
</P>
<P>
In the past few years, Zhu said, bilateral high-level exchanges
have increased, and remarkable progress has been made in bilateral
economic and trade cooperation, as well as scientific,
technological and cultural exchanges.
</P>
<P>
The economies of the two countries are highly complementary and
still have potential for bilateral economic cooperation, Zhu noted.
</P>
<P>
Praising Italy's small- and medium-sized enterprises for their
vigor and distinct characteristics, Zhu said that China can learn
a lot from Italy in this regard, as many Chinese small- and
medium-sized enterprises need to be upgraded.
</P>
<P>
Prodi said that Italy-China relations have a long history, and
bilateral political relations are good. Furthermore, the two
countries share close cooperation in the economy, science and
technology and culture. Bilateral economic cooperation was
fruitful during '80s, he said.
</P>
<P>
Over the past year, such a close cooperative relationship
between the two sides has been restored and developed, he said.
</P>
<P>
Noting that the Italian government regards China as an
important cooperative partner, Prodi said that the Italian
government will focus on the important events taking place in
China in 1997.
</P>
<P>
He said that Italy will make energetic efforts to raise
bilateral relations to a new level by expanding bilateral
cooperation in various areas, including politics, economy, trade,
science and technology, and culture, he said.
</P>
<P>
He revealed that at the end of this year, Italy will hold a
large exhibition in China in a move to introduce Italy to the
Chinese people.
</P>
<P>
Saying that bilateral economic and trade cooperation has great
potential, Prodi noted that the two sides, while making the best
use of their similarities, can conduct more in-depth and overall
cooperation in new ways and forms.
</P>
<P>
Italian small- and medium-sized enterprises have advanced
technology, and the two countries can step up technological
cooperation in this regard, Prodi said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
