<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets Italian Prime Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 6 (Xinhua) -- President Jiang Zemin said here
today that China and Italy should make concerted efforts to
actively push forward the development of bilateral friendly and
cooperative relations for the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
Jiang made the remark here this morning when meeting with
visiting Italian Prime Minister Romano Prodi.
</P>
<P>
Expressing his pleasure at meeting with Prodi, Jiang noted that
Italy enjoys a long history and splendid culture, and the Italian
people have made outstanding contributions to human civilization
and social progress, citing some Italian scientists and artists
like Galileo, Dante, Leonardo da Vinci and Michelangelo Buonarroti.
</P>
<P>
Although China and Italy are far away from each other, the
traditional friendship between the two peoples dates back to
ancient times, he said, adding that Marco Polo is well known among
Chinese people for his great contributions to the exchanges
between the East and the West.
</P>
<P>
Recalling his visit to Italy, Jiang said that Italian culture,
arts, and science and technology left him with a deep impression.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that since China and Italy set up diplomatic ties in
1970, bilateral relations have had a rapid development and leaders
of the two countries have kept constant contacts.
</P>
<P>
Bilateral exchanges and cooperation in politics, economy,
trade, science and technology, and culture have been continuously
developed and bilateral cooperative spheres have continued to
expand, added Jiang.
</P>
<P>
Noting that the two economies have their own characteristics,
Jiang pointed out that Italy has its own advantages in a number of
areas which are priority areas for China's development and worth
China's learning, such as advanced technologies and management
experiences.
</P>
<P>
Jiang noted that the development of bilateral friendly
relations of cooperation have a broad prospect.
</P>
<P>
Stressing that China has always paid much attention to its
friendly relations and cooperation with Italy, Jiang said that the
two countries share identical or similar views on many major
international issues, and a full range of common interests in
seeking for peace and promoting development, despite the
differences between their social systems, historical, and cultural
traditions, and economic development.
</P>
<P>
Under the multi-polarization of the current world, Jiang said,
all countries should respect each other, seek common ground while
reserving differences, strengthen cooperation, and promote a
common development.
</P>
<P>
The establishment of a long-term stable Sino-Italian
relationship is not only in conformity with the common aspiration
and fundamental interests of the two peoples, but also conducive
to world peace, stability, and prosperity.
</P>
<P>
Saying that this is his first visit to China as Italian Prime
Minister, Prodi said that Italy-China friendship and cooperation
had been in the first place among Sino-European relations in the
past, while in the past few years, the development of Italy-China
relations has slowed.
</P>
<P>
He said his current visit here is to be a new opportunity for
the two sides to restore and further develop bilateral cooperative
relations.
</P>
<P>
During this visit, Prodi said, he and Chinese leaders have
conducted a wide-range of in-depth discussions on the development
trend for bilateral cooperation in politics, economy, trade,
science and technology, and culture.
</P>
<P>
He also held talks with China's concerned departments, which
were conducive and fruitful.
</P>
<P>
Noting that Italy, with its own characteristics, is different
from other European countries, Prodi pointed out that bilateral
cooperations should also have their own characteristics.
</P>
<P>
Italian small- and medium-sized enterprises have advanced
technologies, and they are willing to conduct cooperation with
their counterparts across China, especially with those enterprises
in China's central and western areas for they share similar
situations with some Italian cities, said Prodi.
</P>
<P>
Besides, both sides can also further strengthen their
cooperation in energy, communications, and telecommunications.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Jiang also asked Prime Minister Prodi to
convey his regards to Italian President Oscar Luigi Scalfaro.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Qiao Shi, chairman of the Standing Committee of the
Chinese National People's Congress (NPC), also met with the
Italian Prime Minister Prodi here this morning. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
