<HEADLINE> DPRK: S. Korean Warships Open Fire at Fishing Boats </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PYONGYANG, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Three South Korean warships
intruded into the territorial waters of the Democratic People's
Republic of Korea (DPRK) on Thursday and opened fire at fishing
boats, the Korean Central News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
"The warships infiltrated from Taeyonphyong Island into the
waters south of Ssanggyo-ri, Kangryong County, South Hwanghae
Province, and surrounded the fishing boats in a bid to kidnap
them," the news agency said.
</P>
<P>
When a naval patrol ship of the Korean People's Army appeared
on the scene, the enemy ships fired shells at the fishing boats
before fleeing south, it said.
</P>
<P>
But the news agency said the military provocation did not
develop into an armed conflict because of "the patience and
self-control" of the soldiers of the Korean People's Army. 
</P>
</TEXT>
