<HEADLINE> Blair Urges EU to Pay More Heed to People's Real Concerns </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, June 6 (Xinhua) -- British Prime Minister Tony Blair urged
the European Union (EU) to pay more attention to people's real
concerns.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks in an article published today by Germany's
mass-circulation tabloid Bild prior to his scheduled brief visit
to Germany.
</P>
<P>
People in Europe often felt as if they were "greatly removed
from the things leading politicians say and do. This has got to
change," Blair said in the article.
</P>
<P>
"We must pay heed to people's real concerns: jobs, crime, the
environment, security. Those are the priorities of the people in
Europe," Blair said.
</P>
<P>
Blair pledged a strong and leading role of Britain in EU in the
future and said that for too long Britain had been marginalized
and had too little influence in Europe. 
</P>
</TEXT>
