<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 175 Persons Taken into Custody by Colombo Police </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan police took 175 persons
into custody in a cordon and search operation in Colombo on
Thursday, according to a senior police source here today.
</P>
<P>
The source said police carried out the search suspecting of
possible rebels of the Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE)
infiltration into the capital city on account of the troops
onslaught now in operation in the northern part of the country.
</P>
<P>
The Operation "Jaya Sikuru" (Sure of Victory) launched by the
government troops on May 13, is aimed at securing a safe land
route from Vavuniya to Kilinochchi area in the north.
</P>
<P>
The source said those taken to custody will have to provide
reasons for their being in Colombo. Any suspicious characters will
be detained, he added.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE rebels have been fighting a guerrilla war against the
government since 1983 for a separate state in the north and east
of the island country.  
</P>
</TEXT>
