<HEADLINE> Uganda's Milk Production Rises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Uganda's milk production has risen
to over 430 million liters so far this year from 240 million
liters in 1996, recording a 79 percent increase.
</P>
<P>
A report from the Private Dairy Sector Development Program in
Uganda said the country's private dairy sector has been largely
boosted by improved genetics in the last three years.
</P>
<P>
Over 4,000 dairy farmers and 50 artificial insemination
technicians have been trained by United States experts in 46
local dairy cooperatives, said the report. 
</P>
