<HEADLINE> Italy-Funded Automotive Filter Company Operational in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 6 (Xinhua) -- An automotive filter company,
involving an investment of five million US dollars from an Italian
consortium, has been established and gone into operation in the
Pudong New Area of Shanghai, China's leading economic center.
</P>
<P>
The company set up by the Italian Universal Filter
International (UFI) group represents the highest technological
level in the production of automotive filters in China. It can
manufacture a type of long-life automotive filter that is altered
every 60,000 kilometers, sources say.
</P>
<P>
The Sofima Automotive Filter (Shanghai) Corporation Ltd. will
export half of its products to the United States, South Africa,
and Australia through the sales network of UFI, said Giorgio
Girondi, president of UFI.
</P>
<P>
And the company will make efforts to expand its domestic
market, he said.
</P>
<P>
"We are confident about the Chinese market," Girondi said.
</P>
