<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, June 6 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar ended
stronger in Sydney today after international investors looking to
buy Foster's Brewing Group Ltd. stock following news that BHP Ltd.
would sell its holding in the brewery bought the local currency.
</P>
<P>
But it was knocked back off its session high on concerns that
tonight's non-farm payrolls release in the United States might
prove bearish for the U.S. monetary policy.
</P>
<P>
