around 671 million Foster's shares to brokers JB Were and ABN Amro
Hoare Govett.
</P>
<P>
Both those brokers mounted an overnight campaign to on-sell the
stock before the Australian markets opened today.
</P>
<P>
Around 55 percent of the trade was to overseas buyers and 45
percent to local buyers.
</P>
<P>
On the cross-rates, the Australian dollar closed at 87.93
Japanese yen from 87.86 and at 1.3148 Deutsche marks from 1.3099.
 
