<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NPC Chairman Meets Visiting Italian Prime Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Qiao Shi, chairman of China's
National People's Congress (NPC) Standing Committee, said China
attaches importance to developing a long-term and stable
relationship with Italy and is ready to increase mutual
cooperation in every field.
</P>
<P>
Meeting with visiting Italian Prime Minister Romano Prodi, Qiao
said that Sino-Italian ties in various areas have been invigorated
in recent years as shown by the frequent contacts maintained by
leaders of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The NPC chairman recalled his Italy tour two months ago, which
he said has left an "unforgettable impression" on him.
</P>
<P>
The exchange between the NPC and the Italian parliament has
also been reinforced along with the development of bilateral
relations, Qiao said.
</P>
<P>
He added that he agrees with Nicola Mancino, president of the
Italian Senate, on the point that the friendly and cooperative
links between NPC and Italian parliament should be further
promoted.
</P>
<P>
Qiao also briefed Prodi on NPC's legislative activities.
</P>
<P>
Prodi said that the past year has seen an increase of visits
between Italian and Chinese leaders, which has created favourable
conditions for expanding bilateral economic cooperation and the
friendship between the two peoples.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister told Qiao that his entourage includes many
Italian entrepreneurs, whose contacts with their Chinese
counterparts would expand and deepen bilateral collaboration.
</P>
<P>
Prodi said that China's NPC has had many achievements in
legislation and expressed the hope that the legislatures of the
two countries would increase contacts and enhance cooperation.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
