<DOCNO> XIE19970606.0143 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Soeharto Appoints Hartono as Information Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian President Soeharto has
appointed army chief Lt. Gen. Hartono as information minister,
replacing Harmoko who will be named state minister for special
affairs, a new cabinet post.
</P>
<P>
State Secretary/Minister Moerdiono said here that the president
will induct Hartono as information minister on June 11 at the
State Palace.
</P>
<P>
He also said that President Soeharto named Lt. Gen. Wiranto,
currently head of the army's strategic command, as new chief of
staff.
</P>
<P>
Wiranto will be assisted by the newly-appointed deputy army
chief of staff Maj. Gen. Subagio, who is currently chief of the
Diponegoro military district command.
</P>
<P>
Moerdiono said that Wiranto and Subagio will be promoted to a
higher rank in the near future, along with the air force chief of
staff, the navy chief of staff and the Indonesian police chief.
</P>
<P>
The president has also named Maj. Gen. Subiono, commander of
the presidential guards, as head of the army's strategic command.
</P>
<P>
On whether Harmoko will continue to be chairman of the House of
Representatives/People's Consultative Assembly, Moerdiono said,
"it is logical for the chairman of a political party which won in
the general election to hold the post."  
</P>
</TEXT>
