<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dagga Haul on Swaziland Prime Minister's Farm </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Swaziland police have found
about 3 kilogram dagga and 18 dagga plants on a farm owned by
prime minister Sibusiso Dlamini.
</P>
<P>
A local daily The Citizen today quoted a Swazi police
spokesman as saying that they had arrested a 27-year-old labourer
in connection with the dagga.
</P>
<P>
The drug is said to have been reported to the prime minister
by workers who found the shrubs growing on an isolated portion of
the farm.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said a "furious" Mr. Dlamini called them and
ordered a team to stake the area out and arrest those
responsible.
</P>
<P>
"We swooped on the farm and arrested the man who planted the
trees after finding dagga on him," said the spokesman.
</P>
</TEXT>
