<HEADLINE> Xiamen Issues Regular Reports On Air Quality </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, June 6 (Xinhua) -- East China's city of Xiamen now
reports its atmospheric conditions to the public every Friday
through the local media.
</P>
<P>
Over the past few years, the city has redoubled its efforts in
air pollution control, and the air quality has maintained the
state's top atmospheric standards for eight consecutive years.
</P>
<P>
However, with the rapid social and economic development, the
sources of air pollution may also increase, and more pollutants
will be discharged into the air, some experts here believe.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, people's demand for clean air is growing with the
improvement of their living conditions.
</P>
<P>
The aim of the weekly air quality report is to put the city's
air condition under the public scrutiny, so as to upgrade the
city's environmental protection work.
</P>
<P>
Xiamen plans to speed up the automatization of its environment
monitoring system and try to provide daily air reports as soon as
possible.  
</P>
