<HEADLINE> New Passenger Transportation Center Operational in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 6 (Xinhua) -- The first-phase project of the
Passenger Transportation Center of Shanghai Port, located at
Wusongkou on the Yangtze River, went into operation today.
</P>
<P>
The transportation center will be important for the development
of Pudong and the area along the Yangtze River, local officials
predicted.
</P>
<P>
The center, jointly developed by the Baoshan District
Government and the Shanghai Port Administration, is one of the ten
major projects for the Shanghai Port.
</P>
<P>
According to the municipal government plan, the emphasis of
development for Wusongkou will be on passenger transportation.
</P>
<P>
The new passenger transportation center covers a designed area
of 22.2 ha and involves a total investment of 1.25 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The whole project, the construction of which started in 1995,
will be completed in ten years. Upon completion, it will have two
passenger traffic wharfs and a high-speed vessel wharf. 
</P>
