<HEADLINE> Japanese Bank Grants Airport Loans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, June 6 (Xinhua) -- The Export-Import Bank of Japan will
grant 100 million U.S. dollars in loans to support construction of
Meilan International Airport in Haikou, capital of South China's
Hainan province.
</P>
<P>
According to an agreement signed recently in Haikou, the loans
will be transferred by the Bank of China Hainan Branch to the
company responsible for airport construction. The money will
mainly be used to purchase equipment and other materials needed in
the construction.
</P>
<P>
The actual building of Meilan International Airport started
this January. According to schedule, 52 sub-projects will be
completed at a budget of 670 million yuan this year.
</P>
<P>
It is expected that main structure of the terminal will be
completed by the end of October, while the installation of
equipment will start in early 1998 and will be finished by the end
of the year.
</P>
<P>
The airport, estimated to cost 2.3 billion yuan (277.11 million
U.S. dollars), was approved for construction by the State Council
in December of 1993. The airport's major equipment will be
imported from abroad and the airport will meet the world's
advanced standards on completion. 
</P>
