<HEADLINE> India's Electronics, Software Exports Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 6 (Xinhua) -- India's export of electronic
products and computer software and services amounted to 2.54
billion U.S. dollars in 1996-97, up by 34 percent from the
previous year, official sources said here today.
</P>
<P>
This is the third successive year that electronics and software
 have been the fastest-growing export business in the country.
</P>
<P>
In the year, the contribution of the electronics and software
sector to India's total exports more than doubled from 3.2 percent
in 1995-96 to 7.7 percent. Besides, the ratio of exports to
production in the sector rose from 15 percent in 1992-93 to 28.2
percent in the fiscal year 1996-97 ending on March 31, 1997.
</P>
<P>
India exported 1.159 billion dollars' worth of computer
software and services in 1996-97, a growth of 46.5 percent in U.S.
dollar terms.  
</P>
</TEXT>
