<HEADLINE> Blue-chips Suffer Major Loss on Dhaka Stock Exchange </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Blue-chips incurred major losses on
the Dhaka Stock Exchange (DSE) on the just-concluded trading week
tumbling the price index by 75.34 points.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark DSE All Share Price Index slid to 1141.34 points
on Thursday from 1216.68 of the previous week's closing.
</P>
<P>
Following a press report showing Beximco Pharmaceuticals as a
bank defaulter, the traditional market leader on DSE lost 20 taka
(about 0.5 U.S. dollars) per share during the week.
</P>
<P>
Another blue-chip Singer Bangladesh shed by 444.28 taka (about
11.1 dollars) and traded at 6274.27 (about 156.8 dollars) at the
valedictory session.
</P>
<P>
Other blue-chips suffering major losses during the period were
Bangladesh Lamps with a loss of 300 taka (about 7.5 dollars),
Chittagong Cement with 118.5 taka (2.9 dollars) and IDLC with 92
taka (about 2.3 dollars) per share.
</P>
<P>
Besides, both buyers and sellers remained very cautious in
selling and buying shares last week prior to the national budget
for 1997-98 fiscal year. The budget would be placed before
Parliament on June 12.
</P>
<P>
Stock brokers and share investors are expecting that the
government may declare some budgetary measures to ensure stability
in the country's capital market, which faced a scam recently.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
