<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thai Banks Adjust Formula for Retail Rates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Major Thai commercial banks have
adjusted their methods to calculate their lending rates for retail
customers after the central bank gave the green light.
</P>
<P>
Currently, Bangkok Bank quotes its minimum retail rates (MRR)
at 13 percent, based on the minimum lending rate (MLR) plus 0.25
margin.
</P>
<P>
Thai Farmers' Bank marks its MRR at 13.25 percent, applying the
formula of MLR plus 0.5 percent, while the Siam Commercial Bank
quotes its MRR at 13.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
Local newspapers said that the Bank of Thailand has allowed
commercial banks to change their interest rate formulas, which
used to be a one-month deposit rate plus 2 percent margin.
</P>
<P>
The formula now is changing to the MLR plus a 4 percent margin
to allow banks to change varying rates according to their credit
risks.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
