<HEADLINE> Property Rights Market Opens in Remote Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, June 6 (Xinhua) -- The Qinghai Provincial Property
Rights Market, opened in Xining, capital of Qinghai. It is first
of its kind in this remote and underdeveloped province in
Northwest China.
</P>
<P>
Luo Yulin, Director of the Provincial Administration of State
Property, told Xinhua that the setting-up of the market will be
helpful to the local economic development and the efficient
operation of state assets in the province.
</P>
<P>
The market, similar to those in other parts of the country,
will provide an overall service for enterprises that want to
transfer state property rights, according to the official.
</P>
<P>
The market will open branches and sub-branches in prefectures
and counties, he said. 
</P>
