<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Photo Show Opens in Lisbon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LISBON, June 5 (Xinhua) -- In the run-up to Hong Kong's return
to China, a photo show entitled "The Present and Future of Hong
Kong" was opened here today.
</P>
<P>
On display are 88 photos, reflecting the history of Hong Kong,
the patriotism of Hong Kong people and their confidence in future
stability and prosperity of Hong Kong after the handover.
</P>
<P>
The 16-day show was co-sponsored by the city authorities of
Lisbon and the Chinese Embassy.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Ambassador Wei Dong told the opening ceremony that the
return of Hong Kong to the motherland is of historic importance to
China.
</P>
<P>
The handover is also important to the world and attracts world
attention, he added.
</P>
<P>
Through the show, people could come to understand the history
of Hong Kong, the Chinese policy of "one country, two systems,
Hong Kong people governing Hong Kong, a high degree of autonomy,
and prosperity and stability", as well as Hong Kong people's
confidence in their future, the ambassador said.
</P>
<P>
"In 25 days, Hong Kong will return to the motherland. The
colonial rule of Hong Kong by Britain which lasted more than one
and a half centuries is coming to an end," Wei said.
</P>
<P>
"I believe, under the guide of the Basic Law (of Hong Kong),
Hong Kong will have a more brilliant future."
</P>
<P>
Portuguese government and Lisbon municipality officials were
present at the opening ceremony. 
</P>
</TEXT>
