<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Northeast Chinese City Rewards Good Advice </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, June 6 (Xinhua) -- The Harbin city government in
Heilongjiang province has awarded 324 good ideas over the past
four years, paying out 50,000 yuan.
</P>
<P>
Harbin set up an office to solicit people's suggestions in
1993, to improve the government's decision-making ability as well
as enhance people's awareness of democracy and participation.
</P>
<P>
The office has received 2,180 suggestions to date, involving
the city's appearance, communications, social security and other
issues, as well as the layout for industrial and agricultural
development, and economic structural adjustment.
</P>
<P>
The city adopted regulations last year to encourage more
suggestions, and financed a reward fund of 400,000 yuan.
</P>
<P>
People have begun to show greater interest in this
campaign. This year the office receives three suggestions a day.
</P>
<P>
Many changes have taken place. As a result of citizens'
suggestions, authorities recently banned lotteries and
firecrackers in urban areas.
</P>
<P>
Most of the suggestions are put forward by more educated
people, the office said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
