<DOCNO> XIE19970606.0209 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shaanxi Develops Hi-tech Zones </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, June 6 (Xinhua) -- The vigorous development of new
hi-technologies in northwest China's Shaanxi province has promoted
local economic development.
</P>
<P>
The Guanzhong new and high-tech development belt, involving new
and high-tech zones in the cities of Xi'an, Baoji, Yangling,
Xianyang, and Weinan, have so far developed 2,500 scientific and
technological enterprises, including 620 sophisticated ones.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1996, the Guanzhong high-tech belt had gained a
output value over 14 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The high-tech belt, headed by the Xi'an new and high-tech
development zone, has brought along the development of a series of
local economic pillar sectors. 
</P>
