<HEADLINE> Thailand's Rice Exports Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Thailand's rice exports declined by
25.43 percent to 1.857 million tons over the first five months
this year compared with the same period last year, according to
Pracha Charutrakulchai, director-general of the Foreign Trade
Department.
</P>
<P>
Pracha was quoted today by local press as saying that the
export drop was brought about the falling world demand for the
grain.
</P>
<P>
Higher rice output of importing countries, such as China,
Indonesia, and Bangladesh, had caused a two-million-ton drop in
the world's rice trade.
</P>
<P>
Pracha predicted Thai rice exports for the year would be well
bellow the target of 5.3 million tons. The new estimate is 4.8
million tons, a monthly average of 400,000 tons, he said.
</P>
