<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thai Bourse to Introduce New Disclosure Rule </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, June 6 (Xinhua) -- The Stock Exchange of Thailand
(SET) will require all listed firms to follow a new rule when they
disclose the launch of treasure stocks, the local press reported
today.
</P>
<P>
The new rule, which is expected to go into operation in the
third quarter this year, is aimed at making the disclosure
procedure more transparent to investors.
</P>
<P>
Under the new rule, listed firms will have to reveal all
relevant information about their independent directors, especially
how many boards they serve on.
</P>
<P>
The measure is to ensure that the independent directors will
have enough time to take care of the interest of the existing
small shareholders of listed companies.
</P>
<P>
The new regulation also will allow newly established
subsidiaries of listed firms to acquire their parent firms'
stocks.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the Thai bourse is planning to implement more
rules next year governing a listed company's appointment of
independent directors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
