<HEADLINE> Shanxi Cracks down on Drug Trafficking </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, June 6 (Xinhua) -- North China's Shanxi province has
intensified its crack-down on drug crimes since the beginning of
the year after increasing amount of drug trafficking in recent
years has aroused its attention.
</P>
<P>
In a period of two months, the province had crashed 809 gangs,
including 63 alleged drug trafficking gangs with 350 members.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, various public security organs had dealt with
344 cases of drug manufacturing and trafficking and arrested a
large number of suspected drug dealers.
</P>
<P>
To work more effectively, the province instigated a large-scale
publicity campaign, calling for all people to combat drug
trafficking. 
