</P>
<P>
 "People's Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- The People's Bank of China (PBC) issued yesterday a circular
prohibiting banks from using funds for the stock market in any way.
</P>
<P>
The central bank ordered all commercial banks to halt all
involvement in trusts, investments and stock businesses within ten
days.
</P>
<P>
Inter-bank borrowing and lending for trust and investment
companies, security dealers, and other non-banking institutions
must come under the strict supervision of PBC branches, the
circular says.
</P>
<P>
-- The newspaper hailed the PBC decision by publishing an
editorial carried by the Financial News. The editorial criticized
the wrong doing that some securities companies and enterprises
made secret deals with a few banking institutes to speculate on
stock trading with credit funds from banks.
</P>
<P>
"Xinhua Daily Telegraph"
</P>
<P>
-- Chinese Premier Li Peng said here today that the further
development of Sino-Italian relations is helpful for the
establishment of a world pattern featuring multi-polarization and
a just and rational new international order for politics and
economy.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese leader made the remark during his talks here
yesterday with Italian Prime Minister Romano Prodi.
</P>
<P>
-- Deng Xiaoping has left abundant and valuable ideological
wealth to the Chinese people and his theory of building socialism
with Chinese characteristics should continue to be practiced,
Chinese leader Qiao Shi urged recently.
</P>
<P>
Qiao, a member of the Standing Committee of the Political
Bureau of the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee,
made the remarks during an inspection tour in Shanxi Province in
the north.
</P>
<P>
"China Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- The central People's government has decided to establish the
"Office of the Commissioner of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs of
the PRC in the HKSAR" in Hong Kong on July 1, 1997. Ma Yuzhen was
appointed as the Commissioner.
</P>
<P>
-- The second trade fair of Asia-Pacific Economic Co-operation
opened today in east China's Yantai city, with China promising a
wider market access for overseas investors.
</P>
