<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Northeast China City Boosts Eye Care Education </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Shenyang is holding a month-long
activity to boost eye care education among city residents as the
International Eye Care Day comes.
</P>
<P>
June 6, the International Eye Care Day, is also China's
national eye care day designated by the Ministry of Health and the
State Eye Diseases Prevention Office.
</P>
<P>
During the one month celebrations, the Shenyang Eye Microscopy
Surgery Center will provide free diagnosis, give information
concerning eye care, and offer eyedrops without charge.
</P>
<P>
A seminar on eye microscopy surgery is to be held in the city
involving experts both at home and abroad. And slides and video
tapes related to eye care will be shown at public places.
</P>
<P>
The city sources reported that 200,000 residents among the
total six million in Shenyang have suffered from eye diseases of
varying degrees.
</P>
<P>
Statistics showed that China now has five million blind people
and six million persons with poor eyesight. 
</P>
</TEXT>
