<HEADLINE> Venezuelan Troops Clash With Colombian Guerrillas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, June 5 (Xinhua) -- One Colombian rebel was killed and
another captured after a small clash erupted between Venezuelan
troops and Colombian guerrillas in a border area Wednesday,
Venezuelan army authorities said.
</P>
<P>
The skirmish occurred when a Venezuelan Army detachment was
patrolling in La Ceiba in the San Camilo municipality of the
western state of Apure.
</P>
<P>
The Colombian rebels opened fire when they found the unexpected
presence of the Venezuelan troops.
</P>
<P>
The guerrillas may have belonged to the National Liberation
Army or to the Revolutionary Armed Forces of Colombia (FARC).
</P>
<P>
The FARC controls several places in the northeastern department
of Arauca, which borders Colombian cities of the Paez and San
Camilo Venezuelan.
</P>
<P>
Previously the Venezuelan army has denounced incursions of
Colombian rebels into Venezuelan territory. 
