<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's First Cellulose Ferment Production Line </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, June 6 (Xinhua) -- China's first cellulose ferment
production line went into operation today in the Ningxia Hui
Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
This puts an end to the country's long reliance on imports
from abroad. According to a local source, cellulose ferment is a
kind of active biological catalyst which can transform rich
cellulose resources into energy, chemicals, and feed products.
</P>
<P>
Cellulose ferment is widely applied to breeding, textiles,
food, brewing, environmental protection, and bio-engineering.
</P>
<P>
The production line was built at a cost of 11.5 million yuan,
and has a designed annual production capacity of 1,000 tons of
cellulose ferment with annual output value forecast at over 80
million yuan.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970606.0244 </DOCNO>
