<HEADLINE> China Eliminated in HK Basketball International </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 6 (Xinhua) -- China became the first victim of
the five-team Henderson Cup Basketball Championship after
suffering its fourth straight loss here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Already with three defeats, China had a last chance to win a
berth in the semi-finals when it took on Hong Kong's Fukien team
Thursday evening. Fukien had also lost three previous matches.
</P>
<P>
In spite of a 36-30 half-time lead, the Chinese failed to keep
the momentum and lost the match 72-69.
</P>
<P>
The top four teams out of the preliminaries are qualified for
the semi-finals.
</P>
<P>
In the other match today, Hong Kong's Winling scored its fourth
consecutive win by beating Seapower 82-72 after leading 38-37 at
the interval.
</P>
<P>
Of the four preliminary matches, Winling remained unbeaten to
top rank in the field, Seapower ranked second with three wins
against one loss and Singapore's Sin Kee Tycoon was third with two
wins and two defeats, followed by Fukien with three defeats and
one win and China which was winless so far.
</P>
<P>
In the semi-finals Friday evening, Winling face Fukien and
Seapower take on Sin Kee Tycoon.
</P>
<P>
The championship final is set for Saturday afternoon.  
</P>
