<HEADLINE> Chase Manhattan Bank Opens Shanghai Branch </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Chase Manhattan Bank, the largest
commercial bank in the United States, recently opened a Shanghai
branch, in China's financial center.
</P>
<P>
The branch will soon move to the Pudong New Area and will apply
to the People's Bank of China to do business in Renminbi yuan, the
Chinese currency, according to the bank.
</P>
<P>
The US bank first did business in Shanghai in the '20s. Then,
after a long period of absence, it became the first
American agent for the Bank of China in 1973.
</P>
<P>
Currently, the bank has branches in Hong Kong and Tianjin, and
an office in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Over the past decade, Chase Manhattan has helped arrange
various kinds of credit worth a total of two billion US dollars
for many projects in the energy, chemical, iron and steel,
metallurgical, mining and aviation industries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
