<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Laid-off Workers Getting Help From Government </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Hebei Province in north China
has been placing greater importance on helping factory workers who
have been laid off find new jobs.
</P>
<P>
Some 223,000 people have been reemployed in the past two
years, since the province started a "Reemployment Program" to
help unemployed workers get new jobs in 1995.
</P>
<P>
Since that time, 608 special training institutions have been set
up in the province, and job agency networks have been organized in
the province's 11 major cities and in all 137 counties.
</P>
<P>
In the process, local enterprises, especially those that have
been restructured through reforms, have worked hard to find places
for the jobless, and more than 45,000 factory workers who lost
their jobs have started businesses of their own. 
</P>
</TEXT>
