<HEADLINE> German Bavarian State Premier Meets Visiting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MUNICH, Germany, June 5 (Xinhua) -- State premier of the German
state of Bavaria, Edmund Stoiber, met with visiting Chinese leader
Li Ruihuan here today.
</P>
<P>
Li, chairman of the National Committee of the Chinese People's
Political Consultative Conference, said he is very glad to start
his seven-day official goodwill visit to Germany from Bavaria, a
state which plays an important role in Sino-German relations.
</P>
<P>
He said it was late Bavarian State Premier Franz Joseph Strauss
who took the lead in visiting China as early as 1975, which paved
the way for the development of relations between China and
Germany, as well as between China and Bavaria.
</P>
<P>
Today, many Bavaria-based large companies have engaged in close
cooperation with China while numerous small- and medium-sized
enterprises in the state have also established business ties with
China, Li said.
</P>
<P>
He added he hopes that with joint efforts, the relations
between China and Bavaria will grow further.
</P>
<P>
Stressing that China is a country of great importance in the
world, Stoiber said he was deeply impressed by China's economic
development when he visited China two years ago.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed the hope that the cooperation would be
strengthened between Bavaria and China's Shandong Province, which
have established sisterly relationship.
</P>
<P>
With unique cultural traditions, Bavaria, the largest German
federal state, has not only well-developed agriculture and
traditional industries, but also boasts many new industries
including aviation and space industries, electronics, and
automobile.
</P>
<P>
China will on June 7 open in Munich, capital of Bavaria, its
second consulate general in Germany, which Li said will play an
important role in promoting the relations between China and
Bavaria. 
</P>
</TEXT>
